        "#Exoplanets Notes\n",
        "Main Idea:\n",
        "This question requires students to combine multiple criteria at once: filtering for planets with a radius near 1.0 radii, equilibrium temperature near 255 kelvin, distance from the host star near 1.0 AU, and a host star temperature near 5,778 kelvin. The challenge is finding what range around each Earth value counts as close enough, which forces students to justify their decisions through critical thinking and learning about the effect of each planet’s features.\n",
        "\n",
        "The pl_masse (planetary mass) column contains a significant amount of missing values, as planet mass is harder to measure than other features and is not available for many confirmed exoplanets. These missing values (NaNs) have been left in intentionally. Mentors should encourage students to identify and address them as part of their data cleaning process (using df.dropNa), rather than treating them as errors in the dataset.\n",
        "\n",
        "Planetary characteristics (dataset columns) - Certain columns like pl_rade, pl_orbsmax, and st_teff can be hard to understand\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "\n"
      ],
